𝐂𝐀𝐋𝐋 𝐅𝐎𝐑 𝐕𝐎𝐋𝐔𝐍𝐓𝐄𝐄𝐑𝐒 — 𝐖𝐀𝐕𝐄 𝟐 | Batch 2028 Capping and Pinning Ceremony
Missed the first wave?
The Capping and Candle Lighting Ceremony for Batch 2028 draws near, and we are once again opening the call for volunteers to help make this milestone truly memorable.
The ceremony will be held on September 20, 2025, at the FEU Main Auditorium. We are inviting Level 1, 3, and 4 students who are willing and available to assist on the day of the event.
If you’re interested in volunteering, kindly fill out the online form through the link below:

🔗: https://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=3F6kgO7V4EaddTfEe-m3zFwnZ6bteFVAsRTjFqtzGpJUNVMzWE8wT1ZEUFU1MjdaNjhJNjZEVlgzMy4u&route=shorturl

Your support is greatly appreciated in making this event a meaningful and a successful one for Batch 2028. 
#MagniningningAngNursing

Publication Material by Rodel Daeniel

𝐇𝐨𝐥𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐦𝐩𝐚𝐧𝐚𝐝𝐚 𝐰𝐡𝐢𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐭'𝐬 𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐦 🤗

Ever wondered what happens when you take a small step closer? Sometimes, the best empanadas are just one hold away. And this one might just be the sign you’ve been waiting for.

Here in FEU Nursing Society, we’re more than just a community—we’re a family that grows, learns, and thrives together. With each event, each bond, and each smile, we’re building something truly meaningful. And guess what? We’d love for you to be part of it.

🔗http://bit.ly/3JKoDjY 

𝐖𝐚𝐫𝐦 𝐧𝐨𝐡? 𝐆𝐚𝐧𝐲𝐚𝐧 𝐬𝐚 𝐍𝐮𝐫𝐒𝐨𝐜 𝐅𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐲, 𝐬𝐨 𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐥𝐲 𝐤𝐚 𝐧𝐚! 🥰
